cereal: arbitrary data types and reversibly turns them into different
cereal: representations, such as compact binary encodings, XML, or JSON.
cereal: It was designed to be fast, light-weight, and easy to extend - it
cereal: has no external dependencies and can be easily bundled with other
cereal: code or used standalone.
